      <p>Chicago's restaurant scene spans from Michelin-starred fine dining to some of the nation's best neighborhood casual concepts. Wicker Park, Logan Square, the West Loop, River North, and Lincoln Park are major dining corridors—each with distinct character and customer demographics. Ethnic neighborhoods (Pilsen, Chinatown, Andersonville, Greektown, Little Village) offer some of the best value dining and most loyal neighborhood customer bases.</p>
